reportspage.METERIALMOVEMENTREPORT: It is the report that the movements of the selected restaurant between the two dates are listed by type.
reportspage.METERIALUSAGEREPORT: Inventory and quantities used between the two dates of the selected restaurant are included
reportspage.INVENTORYUSAGES: In the report, you can see the number of items used and inventory-product links between the two dates of the restaurant you selected.
reportspage.ACTUALCALCULATEREMAINDERLIST: Inventory movements according to label type (count, input, output,used, difference, etc.) between the two dates of the restaurant you selected in the report) is the report in which they are all shown in a single list.
reportspage.ACTUALCALCULATED: In this report, the beginning of the period value of the total material in the warehouse between the dates selected, the semi-finished stock, if any, the total input material, the total used material, the amount calculated as a result of the total output material, the actual amount of material in the warehouse are seen.
reportspage.USAGEREPORT: In this report, information on which material was used in which product, number of prescriptions and number of products are included in the selected date ranges. You can select the desired group from the label selection field or an inventory from the material field to list only that group or inventory by filtering.
reportspage.BALANCELIST: This is the report where we will display the quantities of material in our stores, such as the actual calculated balance list.
reportspage.INVENTORYWASTECONSUPTIONS: You can see the inventory waste amounts between the dates you choose.
reportspage.INVENTORYCOST: It is the report that the ideal and realized cost values of all branches are given during the active period.
reportspage.INVENTORYPERIODICCOST: It is the report that gives the ideal and realized cost values between the selected dates.
reportspage.INVENTORYRECIPES: If you have not made any inventory selections during the selected period, the prescriptions for all products are listed.
reportspage.INVENTORYUSAGEDETAIL: Gives you inventory usage details of the date range you selected and the sales the restaurant made in that date range.
reportspage.DOUGHCHART: This is the report that takes the sales quantities of the last four weeks and gives the estimated dough quantities according to the average.
reportspage.DOUGHCHARTDATA: It is the report that the number of uses is given in the week on the selected date.
reportspage.DAILYORGANIZATIONCHART: It is the report that gives the day-based average of the materials used in the branch in the last four weeks.
reportspage.INVENTORYCOSTSUMMARY: It is the summary report in which the ideal and realized cost values are given in the selected period.
reportspage.FOODCOSTBYTORDERSOURCE: It is the report that food costs are given according to order types and order sources.
reportspage.CUSTOMERLIST: This is the report where you can see customers placing orders between selected dates.
reportspage.ORDERLISTREPORT: The report lists all orders of your chosen restaurant between the two dates.
reportspage.NEWCUSTOMERS: The report gives the customer data of the restaurant of your choice who placed their first order between the two dates.
reportspage.REGIONANALISYS: From the grouping area, you can select the report grouping as neighborhood or grid. The report returns the aggregate region analysis data for the restaurant you selected between the two dates and the system.
reportspage.SERVICESAREAREPORT: It is the report that gives all the index data defined to the selected restaurant.
reportspage.CUSTOMERCONSUPTIONREPORT: Returns customer consumption (number of receipts, total amount, last order date, number of inactive days, customer creation dates) between selected dates. You can filter from selected fields and get the report according to those properties.
reportspage.CUSTOMERSEGMENTATIONREPORT: The report provides information such as the number of active customer orders for the last 3 months of the selected year and month.
reportspage.CASHREPORT: All orders that have been paid off for the restaurant on the selected date appear as units and amounts.
reportspage.STORECASHREPORT: Icmals for the restaurant on the selected date can be checked from this report. If (-) or (+) amount except 0 in the difference field, this means that the case is different. (- ) case deficit, ( + ) case surplus can be considered.
reportspage.ORDERPAYMENTS: It is the report that the total of orders can be seen according to the payment types realized for the restaurant between the selected dates.
reportspage.TURNOVERBYDAYSREPORT: Total turnover of all the restaurants you are authorized between selected dates tc etc. it is the report in which their information is given.
reportspage.TRENDSREPORT: This is the report that lists the restaurants you are authorized for Today, last week, previous day, monthly turnover, ac, tc values and calculated trend values.
reportspage.ACCOUNTBALANCEREPORT: Customers with current debt for the selected restaurant are listed.
reportspage.CUMULATIVESALES: A report that returns cumulative totals based on the selected date.
reportspage.STORERANKING: It is the report that gives monthly branch rankings.
reportspage.SALESBYSOURCE: It is a report in which sales percentages are given according to order types and order sources.
reportspage.PRODUCTUSAGECOUNTS: It is the report that lists products sold between selected dates.
reportspage.STORESALESSTATISTICS: It is the report that the order total, number and order numbers and percentages of certain product groups are given between the selected dates.
reportspage.PRODUCTSALESSTATISTICS: You can view product sales statistics with different templates between selected dates.
reportspage.PRODUCTWITHRELATIONS: You can see the menu sub-details between the selected dates from this report.
reportspage.MENUINCOME: You can see the information such as how many items were sold and the price of the product in which campaign between the selected dates.
reportspage.PRODUCTCOSTDETAILS: This is the report in which the quantity, price and cost information of the defined materials are given in the product field.
reportspage.PRODUCTSALESPIVOT: It is the report that the units and totals of the products sold are given. It can be filtered by product and product groups.
reportspage.USERPRODUCTSALES: It is the report that the units and totals of the products sold based on the user according to the templates are given.
reportspage.PRODUCTSALESPOCHETTE: It is the report of the quantity and quantity totals of the carry bags sold.
reportspage.ORDERDRIVERLIST: Among the dates selected is the report that orders on the bikers were placed.
reportspage.ORDERPERFORMANCE: It is the report that package order times are given between the selected dates.
reportspage.ORDERLOGS: A log report listing all orders steps and updates between selected dates.
reportspage.RETURNLIST: It is the report that the product quantities in the cancelled orders are given.
reportspage.RETURNLISTDETAIL: It is the report in which the product quantities, amounts, order source, canceling user information and cancellation note are given in detail in the cancelled orders.
reportspage.DELETEDORDERITEMS: It is the report that lists the products entered into the order between the selected dates and then deleted from the order items.
reportspage.ORDERPROMOTIONREPORT: In this report you can see how much discount is added to which order between the selected dates and with which code..
reportspage.ORDERTOTALS: You can see the total and quantity distributions of order types between the selected dates.
reportspage.KITCHENPERFORMANCE: It is the report in which the preparation,firing,waiting,exit times of all orders are calculated between the selected dates.
reportspage.ORDERLASTATES: It is the report that the order status of all authorized restaurants between the selected dates is given in units and amount distributions.
reportspage.PROMOTIONCODEDETAILS: It is the report that gives the date, order and customer use of the selected promotion.
reportspage.ORDERPAYMENTSCHECK: It is the report that gives the date, order and customer use of the selected payment type.
reportspage.COMPLAINTLISTREPORTS: List of complaints entered between selected dates.
reportspage.SMSLIST: It is the report that lists all customers of the selected restaurant who have given sms approval.
reportspage.GENERALSMSLIST: List of customers who have given sms approval between selected dates
reportspage.STORELOGS: It is the report that shows changes made to the settings of the branches between selected dates and by whom.
reportspage.STOREANALISYSDETAIL: Turnover, tc, ac, order status times, etc.of all authorized restaurants between selected dates. it is the report in which the information is given.
reportspage.INVENTORYBALANCELIST: It is the report that shows how much is used from which inventory according to the branch at the end of the period.
reportspage.REALPAYMENTSPIVOT: The report shows the total turnover of all authorized restaurants according to the actual payments between the selected dates.
reportspage.UNPAIDDELIVERIES: It is the report that lists the unpaid invoices for the selected restaurant.
reportspage.STAFFSHIFTDIFF: Returns the scheduled, realized shift hours and difference based on the user roles of the selected week.
reportspage.DIFFBYHOUR: The report gives an average of 13 weeks for the days of the selected week, indicating the total need.
reportspage.SHIFTPERSONTOTALS: It is the report that gives you the number of days and hours of the user's shift based on the given date range.
reportspage.SHIFTACTUALTOTALS: It is the report that gives the day-based sum of the branch and the number of days and hours of the user's shifts according to the selected week.
reportspage.WEEKLYANALYSIS: It is the report that gives the difference and need on a daily and hourly basis of the selected week and restaurant.
